			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				90% of all bard songs with the exceptions of things such as charm, last for 3 ticks, a song ticks every 3 seconds so each song lasts nine seconds, which means, 1,2,3 tick, song off another on,1,2,3 tick switch back to other song, both will last nine seconds and you should waste no more than 7 seconds between the first tick of one song and the second tick of that song. Keeping both in tact. As the guy below said, selo's and chant of battle are a good example. If you're really good and experienced you can waste less than a second switching from one song to another after one ticks which will enable you to keep the effects of 3 songs going at the time. Unfortunatly the information you heard, guy below, is wrong, it's impossible to twist 4 songs, 3 is the max and it takes alot of experience to do that right. I've been doing it for say 30 levels now and I lose effects of songs quick. songs I twist the most are, Selo's consistant chain,(bard snare level 24&gt;, appauling screetch(fear close range level 26) and Jonathan's whistling warsong(self haste str boost don't remember the level). I lose snare quite often and the creature will be feared and run off, most creatures I fight move faster than normal so I do not start to chase considering fear will wear in 3 or 4 more seconds after snare does i just wait for him to come back.<BR>
<BR>
Sorry for the ranting just thought I'd clear it up a lil : )<BR>
