	<tr>
		
			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				Well Jinar,<BR>
<BR>
here's a guide to twisting songs:<BR>
<BR>
Since you lvl 4 you won't have much benifit of it.<BR>
But things start to get interesting at 5th, 6th lvl (your close)<BR>
Here we go:<BR>
<BR>
Twisting is combining songs, the idea is to start a song. Then stop it to start a next song. A song always (the most of them) last a while after you stop them. The trick is to time the stopping and starting in time (about 4 seconds) so you can have the benifit of both songs. You bassacly keep changing song during a fight. (This is where hotkeys come into play) <BR>
<BR>
For example, while you have your Chant on, you can twisk it with Selo's (lvl 5) to get the bonus from Chant of Battle (ac, dex) as well as Selo's (fast running). <BR>
<BR>
With a bit of practice it is possible to twist 3 (i even heard 4) songs at a time.<BR>
<BR>
Good luck,<BR>
<BR>
Corbolu, 8th season bard <BR>
Tallon Zek<BR>
<BR>
p.s Another word of advice, when you get you instruments, put your primary, secondary weapons, your instrument(s) and a empty in your hotkeys. That makes using instument easier (swap, prim for instr and instr for secon and secon in empty)<BR>
<BR>
That's all for now, all bard out there rule!!!<BR>

				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
